Kim Jong Un, the top leader of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), sent a message to Chinese President Xi Jinping on Friday to congratulate China on a successful opening of the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics, according to the official Korean Central News Agency. The opening ceremony is scheduled for Friday night in the Chinese capital. In his message, Kim also extended greetings to the Chinese leader, the Communist Party of China, the government and all Chinese people.